  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-04-27",
    "date": "2009-05-18T18:27:23Z",
    "text": "Correspondence With Our Heroes Act - Directs the Secretary of Defense to provide for a one-year program under which postal benefit vouchers are provided for the benefit of members of the Armed Forces on active duty in Iraq or Afghanistan, or hospitalized at a military facility as a result of a disease or injury incurred as a result of such service. Entitles voucher users to make free mailings to such individuals. Limits vouchers to one per month.\n\nRequires the Department of Defense (DOD) to transfer to the Postal Service an amount representing the amount of the vouchers used."
  },
